by Khoronzon » Wed Oct 21, 2020 9:15 am

Twithe Gilakish Republic wrote:GDP-wise, West Reveria would be the fifth most powerful country in Africa, with its GDP per capita being about more than 2.5 times the next highest.

For one thing, I learned that "folkwealdery" doesn't always replace "democracy" despite being its linguistic counterpart. It seems like "democracy" is mostly used for formal ideological names ("Democratish Socialism" instead of "Folkwealdy Socialism"), while "folkwealdery" is for pretty much everything else. I also learned that Gilan had a period of independence as a socialist republic prior to its current iteration, hence its currently being known as the "Twithe Republic", which was established as the First World War was ongoing by a working-class movement led by Mirza Kuchak Khan, eventually with the backing of the Russian Red Army, in response to landowners plundering the country. During its existence as the First Republic, it provided considerable assistance to Iran in the form of food aid during a famine as well as retaking Iranian territories that Russia had previously conquered. Despite its attempts at pleasing the Iranian state, though, the First Republic was eventually overthrown by the Iranian army and made a province of Iran.

Kiu Ghesik wrote:They've explicitly targeted rioters in military operations before.

Despite being generally referred to as "short swords" instead of "knives" because of their length, the way Ghesites use blades in combat is very much along the lines of knife fighting, taking place at very close ranges in only desperate situations and combining the blade itself with hand-to-hand techniques such as wrestling. It completely goes against the way Ghesites are used to fighting, which is precisely why it's so important to them, since its role is as a last resort when their standard methods can't be used.
